00:10:49.510 --> 00:10:52.060
And the afternoon panel
is entitled citizenship

00:10:52.060 --> 00:10:52.630
on the move.

00:10:52.630 --> 00:10:55.300
It speaks to the
fluidity of citizenship,

00:10:55.300 --> 00:11:00.280
it's unruliness in a world
of rule, if you will.

00:11:00.280 --> 00:11:03.830
It talks about citizenship
in our ever more mobile world

00:11:03.830 --> 00:11:05.420
where the migrant
and the refugee

00:11:05.420 --> 00:11:08.570
challenge the notions of
citizenship governed by nation

00:11:08.570 --> 00:11:10.610
states and call
upon us to rethink

00:11:10.610 --> 00:11:12.930
the geography of community.

00:11:12.930 --> 00:11:15.620
We'll consider
citizenship in communities

00:11:15.620 --> 00:11:17.930
that pre-date colonial
and settler state

00:11:17.930 --> 00:11:20.930
borders and even the
categories of citizenship

00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:23.520
fashioned by those societies.

00:11:23.520 --> 00:11:25.340
And we'll hear how
white Americans consider

00:11:25.340 --> 00:11:28.130
their own identity under
threat and how some of them

00:11:28.130 --> 00:11:31.350
are redefining that identity
and a form of citizenship

00:11:31.350 --> 00:11:35.330
in increasingly racialized
and eugenic ways.

00:11:35.330 --> 00:11:37.430
There are, of course,
themes, many of them

00:11:37.430 --> 00:11:39.320
that we could've
included or interrogated

00:11:39.320 --> 00:11:40.940
more profoundly today.

00:11:40.940 --> 00:11:43.700
What is global
citizenship, for instance?

00:11:43.700 --> 00:11:45.530
That is, for what
it's worth, a question

00:11:45.530 --> 00:11:47.720
that we addressed directly
at last year's gender

00:11:47.720 --> 00:11:50.300
and citizenship conference.

00:11:50.300 --> 00:11:53.220
It figures not as explicitly
in today's discussions,

00:11:53.220 --> 00:11:55.250
but it's always there.

00:11:55.250 --> 00:11:57.500
How has war and
military service,

00:11:57.500 --> 00:12:00.960
or how have they
defined citizenship?

00:12:00.960 --> 00:12:04.080
What is the proper balance
between rights and duties

00:12:04.080 --> 00:12:05.520
in thinking about citizenship?

00:12:05.520 --> 00:12:07.770
And what is the
role of education

00:12:07.770 --> 00:12:10.650
in attaining or promoting the
flourishing of citizenship,

00:12:10.650 --> 00:12:14.150
the optimal balance in that way?

00:12:14.150 --> 00:12:15.860
One could also talk
about other areas

00:12:15.860 --> 00:12:18.350
of our planet such as
India and its caste system

00:12:18.350 --> 00:12:21.380
regulating citizenship
for millennia and the way

00:12:21.380 --> 00:12:25.220
that those kinds of systems
have powerful legacies today.

00:12:25.220 --> 00:12:27.230
Our discussions
today are necessarily

00:12:27.230 --> 00:12:30.860
