01:16:25.300 --> 01:16:29.980
- You know, we fought
really hard for citizenship

01:16:29.980 --> 01:16:32.260
because we wanted to control
the institutions that

01:16:32.260 --> 01:16:33.770
were controlling our lives.

01:16:33.770 --> 01:16:36.010
And if we didn't have
the right to vote,

01:16:36.010 --> 01:16:38.380
then we couldn't
become legislators,

01:16:38.380 --> 01:16:43.030
we couldn't become
teachers, what not,

01:16:43.030 --> 01:16:44.980
controlling those institutions.

01:16:44.980 --> 01:16:47.680
But yet, what happened
was that in order

01:16:47.680 --> 01:16:53.380
to become citizens and
have the right to vote,

01:16:53.380 --> 01:16:56.110
it meant that we had to start
losing some of the things

01:16:56.110 --> 01:16:58.210
that we had as
indigenous people.

01:16:58.210 --> 01:17:01.270
And we had these examples
where our people would

01:17:01.270 --> 01:17:05.440
practice learning English.

01:17:05.440 --> 01:17:09.670
And they have these sessions,
and they'd all say, spell cat.

01:17:09.670 --> 01:17:14.380
C-A-T. C-A-T. C-A-T. Then
they would have a test.

01:17:14.380 --> 01:17:15.880
Who can spell cat?

01:17:15.880 --> 01:17:18.370
Somebody would raise their
hand and says, I can.

01:17:18.370 --> 01:17:21.640
A-C-T. A-C-T. A-C-T.

01:17:21.640 --> 01:17:25.570
So in going for
something that we thought

01:17:25.570 --> 01:17:27.140
was going to be
beneficial to us,

01:17:27.140 --> 01:17:29.410
we found out that we
were losing things.

01:17:29.410 --> 01:17:31.390
The same thing in the
native corporations.

01:17:31.390 --> 01:17:35.080
We wanted to have control over
our land and our resources.

01:17:35.080 --> 01:17:38.320
And we did not want
to have the government

01:17:38.320 --> 01:17:40.990
say that this is what you
can do with your lands.

01:17:40.990 --> 01:17:43.480
We found out from our
brothers and sisters

01:17:43.480 --> 01:17:46.670
in the lower 48 that
had reservations.

01:17:46.670 --> 01:17:49.425
Our vets would come back
home, and they would find out

01:17:49.425 --> 01:17:50.800
that the Bureau
of Indian Affairs

01:17:50.800 --> 01:17:54.430
had leased out their lands
to ranchers and farmers.

01:17:54.430 --> 01:17:57.470
And so we said we
don't want to do that.

01:17:57.470 --> 01:18:00.910
And so we went for
a fee-simple title,

01:18:00.910 --> 01:18:02.500
and we went for corporations.

01:18:02.500 --> 01:18:04.720
We didn't know what
corporations were.

01:18:04.720 --> 01:18:07.210
But we knew that under
corporations, you

01:18:07.210 --> 01:18:10.250
could hold land under
fee-simple title.

01:18:10.250 --> 01:18:13.420
But then we found out
that, well, that means

01:18:13.420 --> 01:18:15.760
you have to develop your land.

01:18:15.760 --> 01:18:19.540
And we didn't want
to develop our land.

01:18:19.540 --> 01:18:25.030
But yet, we were supposed to
be profit making corporations.

01:18:25.030 --> 01:18:27.370
And so we found out
that a lot of times,

01:18:27.370 --> 01:18:30.760
we had a lot of
internal conflicts.

01:18:30.760 --> 01:18:32.860
And so we went to
Congress, and we

01:18:32.860 --> 01:18:36.070
said, OK, let's create
land banks so that we could

01:18:36.070 --> 01:18:38.830
put our land into land
banks so we wouldn't

01:18:38.830 --> 01:18:42.220
have to develop the land so
that they wouldn't be taxable.

01:18:44.770 --> 01:18:49.390
So what happened was that we
were looking for a benefit,

01:18:49.390 --> 01:18:52.240
but then we'd find
out that it was offset

01:18:52.240 --> 01:18:55.210
by something, some requirement.

01:18:55.210 --> 01:18:59.470
In our area, we have trees.

01:18:59.470 --> 01:19:02.560
We live in a
beautiful rain forest.

01:19:02.560 --> 01:19:07.190
And so we started
harvesting trees.

01:19:07.190 --> 01:19:10.530
And we didn't feel
good about it either.

01:19:10.530 --> 01:19:11.300
Let me tell you.

01:19:11.300 --> 01:19:13.330
We shouldn't feel
good, but we knew

01:19:13.330 --> 01:19:18.760
it was our duty to be making
some money for our people

01:19:18.760 --> 01:19:21.970
and giving them dividends,
providing them jobs.

01:19:21.970 --> 01:19:25.270
And we would do these
tree ceremonies.

01:19:25.270 --> 01:19:28.930
And here we are thanking
the spirit of the trees

01:19:28.930 --> 01:19:31.450
for allowing us to use them.

01:19:31.450 --> 01:19:33.760
But then when we
saw that we almost

01:19:33.760 --> 01:19:39.280
cut down all of our old growth,
we said something's wrong here.

01:19:39.280 --> 01:19:43.900
So we actually went on a
retreat and said, what do we do?

01:19:43.900 --> 01:19:47.420
We're conflicting with our
own core cultural values.

01:19:47.420 --> 01:19:50.200
So it was about 15
years ago that we really

01:19:50.200 --> 01:19:54.640
did a reassessment of where
we're going as native people

01:19:54.640 --> 01:19:56.830
with these native corporations.

01:19:56.830 --> 01:20:00.220
And we also found out we weren't
getting rid of poverty either.

01:20:00.220 --> 01:20:03.550
We still are very
impoverished people.

01:20:03.550 --> 01:20:12.400
And so we said, OK, how
do we harvest our trees

01:20:12.400 --> 01:20:13.840
without cutting them down?

01:20:13.840 --> 01:20:17.230
How do we make money
without cutting them down?

01:20:17.230 --> 01:20:21.490
So we started searching
forest certification.

01:20:21.490 --> 01:20:23.920
We started studying
mitigation banks.

01:20:23.920 --> 01:20:27.850
We started studying
carbon sequestration.

01:20:27.850 --> 01:20:30.100
And I tell you, I
was so proud when we

01:20:30.100 --> 01:20:32.230
got into carbon sequestration.

01:20:32.230 --> 01:20:35.140
But then my granddaughter
comes home and says,

01:20:35.140 --> 01:20:37.733
look at what you're
doing to this earth.

01:20:37.733 --> 01:20:39.400
Look at what you're
doing to this earth.

01:20:39.400 --> 01:20:40.990
I thought we were
doing something good

01:20:40.990 --> 01:20:42.890
with carbon sequestration.

01:20:42.890 --> 01:20:46.000
So for us, it's been
this whole dilemma

01:20:46.000 --> 01:20:50.560
of trying to figure out how
do we live in this world?

01:20:50.560 --> 01:20:53.350
And we brought our core
cultural balance values back

01:20:53.350 --> 01:20:56.710
to the forefront.

01:20:56.710 --> 01:20:58.900
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]
means "our land."

01:20:58.900 --> 01:21:03.880
It means we have this spiritual
relationship to the land.

01:21:03.880 --> 01:21:06.850
But it also means
we utilize the land.

01:21:06.850 --> 01:21:09.070
So we found out
you know that are

01:21:09.070 --> 01:21:12.400
our traditional religious
practices were not

01:21:12.400 --> 01:21:17.090
going to mitigate the negative
impacts on our environment.

01:21:17.090 --> 01:21:19.450
So we ended up hiring
teams of scientists

01:21:19.450 --> 01:21:21.280
to try to help us figure out.

01:21:21.280 --> 01:21:25.380
Anyway, we're right
in the midst all

01:21:25.380 --> 01:21:28.440
of this trying to figure
out how do we maintain

01:21:28.440 --> 01:21:30.130
our core cultural values?

01:21:30.130 --> 01:21:32.850
How do we make sure that
our land is protected

01:21:32.850 --> 01:21:35.490
for future generations
and in accordance

01:21:35.490 --> 01:21:39.570
with one of our other
core cultural values?

01:21:39.570 --> 01:21:42.510
I think we have a
lot of dilemmas.

01:21:42.510 --> 01:21:47.520
But what I think is that we're
fortunate in that we still

01:21:47.520 --> 01:21:49.800
have measure of
control where we're

01:21:49.800 --> 01:21:52.020
trying to figure out things.

01:21:52.020 --> 01:21:53.580
But one of the
things we learned is

01:21:53.580 --> 01:21:56.490
we need to have our
children educated.

01:21:56.490 --> 01:22:01.410
And so we're sending our kids
off to school and saying,

01:22:01.410 --> 01:22:04.860
we need to figure out how do
we live in this New World?

01:22:04.860 --> 01:22:06.720
And I want to thank
Harvard for educating

01:22:06.720 --> 01:22:10.350
a lot of our tribal members
from southeast Alaska.

01:22:10.350 --> 01:22:12.420
But it's a journey
that we're on.

01:22:12.420 --> 01:22:14.160
I don't have all of the answers.

01:22:14.160 --> 01:22:18.300
But I do know that we have
core cultural values that

01:22:18.300 --> 01:22:22.680
have sustained us in our
homeland for 10,000 years.

01:22:22.680 --> 01:22:25.680
We know that conclusively
and scientifically.

01:22:25.680 --> 01:22:27.250
So we're trying
to figure it out.

01:22:27.250 --> 01:22:28.835
But we don't have
all the answers.

01:22:28.835 --> 01:22:29.460
- That's great.

01:22:29.460 --> 01:22:32.310
Just to pick up on a
couple of those themes,

01:22:32.310 --> 01:22:34.558
I mean, I think this idea
of citizenship and control

01:22:34.558 --> 01:22:36.600
and the way in which that
control then is further

01:22:36.600 --> 01:22:40.680
conditioned or restricted is
really powerful and a through

01:22:40.680 --> 01:22:42.190
