01:22:42.190 --> 01:22:44.310
I think in some
ways what we're all

01:22:44.310 --> 01:22:49.710
touching upon is that for
citizenship to be real,

01:22:49.710 --> 01:22:54.450
to have real meaning and force,
that democratic control has

01:22:54.450 --> 01:22:58.350
to spread well beyond the
kind of formal political realm

01:22:58.350 --> 01:23:02.340
to respond to these other
types of conditioning

01:23:02.340 --> 01:23:05.170
or restricting of voice
and accountability.

01:23:05.170 --> 01:23:07.850
And so even if we think about--

01:23:07.850 --> 01:23:11.220
in some ways, the
exclusion of membership

01:23:11.220 --> 01:23:12.690
has this hydraulics to it.

01:23:12.690 --> 01:23:15.300
You can gain control and
membership in one domain,

01:23:15.300 --> 01:23:17.850
but then have the rug
pulled out from under you

01:23:17.850 --> 01:23:18.900
in another domain.

01:23:18.900 --> 01:23:20.880
Gain political
voice, but then you

01:23:20.880 --> 01:23:23.400
don't have economic voice,
or vise versa, right?

01:23:23.400 --> 01:23:26.400
And so that kind of
sense of whack-a-mole

01:23:26.400 --> 01:23:30.420
is I think part of what we're
all trying to trying to get at.

01:23:30.420 --> 01:23:32.550
I think maybe the last
thing I'll add here

01:23:32.550 --> 01:23:38.460
is that I think the unmasking of
those hidden forms of control,

01:23:38.460 --> 01:23:41.490
whether it's through the
conditions attached to property

01:23:41.490 --> 01:23:46.050
claims or the kind of private
governance of the platforms

01:23:46.050 --> 01:23:48.240
